  "text": "Mitochondria are limited by the usual doublemembraned envelope. Characteristically, the invaginati0ns of the inner membrane which form the cristae are tubular or villus-like rather than plate-like (Figs. l, 2, and 14) . Electron-opaque globuli (of [CITATION_1] appear to be present in small quantities in those genera examined. The shape of the mitochondria is highly variable, and there is no apparent association of the mitochondria with other organelles. In Chorda the mitochondria tend to lie along the margin of the cell, while in Fucus and Giffordla they are randomly scattered throughout.",
